19/09/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- An employee suffered minor injuries Monday (19 September) when a suspected letter bomb exploded inside the mailroom of the British embassy in Zagreb. The worker -- a local man -- received "very minor injuries" in the early morning blast, according to the UK Foreign Office. A spokesman said he was unaware of any threats to the embassy, but security has been stepped up. 
In other news, local media is reporting that political directors in the EU Troika met in New York on Sunday, to discuss Croatia's bid for EU accession. War crimes co-operation remains the sticking point in membership talks. The Troika includes representatives of the past, present and future holder of the rotating EU presidency. (BBC, HINA, index.hr - 19/09/05)
